Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editChangeMask(25.10)                                    editChangeMask(25.10)

Name
       editChangeMask  - Changes the mask for the selected wires, vias, physi-
       cal pins, or trim metal to the specified color

Syntax
       editChangeMask

       [-help]

       {-to {0 1 2} | [[-top {0 1 2}] [-bottom {0 1 2}]  [-cut  {0  1  2}]]  |
       -trim_metal {0 1 2}}

       Changes  the  mask for the selected wires, vias, physical pins, or trim
       metal to the specified color.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editChangeMask parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editChangeMask

       -bottom {0 1 2}
              Changes the mask for the bottom layer of the  selected  vias  to
              the specified color.

       -cut {0 1 2}
              Changes  the  mask for the cut layer of the selected vias to the
              specified color.

       -to {0 1 2}
              Changes the mask for the selected wires and physical pins to the
              specified color.

       -top {0 1 2}
              Changes the mask for the bottom layer of the  selected  vias  to
              the specified color.

       -trim_metal {0 1 2}
              Changes  the mask for the trim metal of the selected patch wires
              to the specified color. If the  trim  metal  being  edited  com-
              pletely  covers another trim metal, the mask of the covered trim
              metal is also changed simultaneously.

Examples
              * The following command changes the mask for the  selected  wire
                and physical pin to 2:

                editChangeMask -to {2}

              * The following command changes the mask for the bottom layer of
                the selected via to 1:

                editChangeMask -bottom {1}

              * The  following  command changes the mask for the trim metal of
                the selected patch wires to 2:

                editChangeMask -trim_metal {2}

